bilingual.source: Is he funny or young or old?
bilingual.target: 他是有趣的、年轻的还是老的？
劳拉·德克尔是一名年轻的水手。
年轻的学习者喜欢大声朗读。

bilingual.source: He could play sports when he was young.
bilingual.target: 他年轻的时候可以做运动。

bilingual.source: Young New Zealanders have become fully involved.
bilingual.target: 年轻的新西兰人已经完全参与进来。

bilingual.source: There were only a few young paper-cutters before.
bilingual.target: 以前只有几个年轻的剪纸艺人。

bilingual.source: This word refers to the years when someone is young.
bilingual.target: 这个词指的是某人年轻的时候。

bilingual.source: The young Pelé played football to his heart's content.
bilingual.target: 年轻的贝利尽情地踢足球。

bilingual.source: I didn't watch a lot of TV when I was young.
bilingual.target: 我年轻的时候不怎么看电视。

list.abstract: 《Young》是一首由Richard Rawson、Pete Ibsen、Ali Tennant作词、作曲，Tulisa演唱的英文歌曲。其发布于2012年3月24日，收录在Tulisa 2012年3月24日月发行的专辑《We are Young》中。
young是一个英语单词，可以用作形容词和名词，可以翻译为年轻人、青年的、有活力的，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: We have bottled all the stars for you this evening, my young friends.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今晚我们已经备好了所有的星星，年轻的朋友们。

yingyinNormal.en: Let me guess, you've heard there's an opening in young Ms. Sparrow's classroom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 让我猜猜，你们听说了年轻的斯帕萝老师的班上有空位了。

yingyinNormal.en: This relatively young volcano has been steadily erupting for over 30 years now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个相对年轻的火山已持续爆发了 30 多年。

yingyinNormal.en: And one day, she and a couple of other young hunters came running in all painted up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有一天，她召集了一些年轻的猎人，他们全副武装。

yingyinNormal.en: Go north, find the Dúnedain. There's a young ranger amongst them. You should meet him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 去北方吧，去找杜内丹人，他们中有一个年轻的游民，你该去结识他。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies》

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, remember, we were young. Hey, Spring break, sophomore year, I got high in my bedroom and my parents walked in and smelled it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 记不记得我们年轻的时候，大二的春假，我在房里正在兴奋，我爸妈走进来闻到了。

yingyinNormal.en: More than a thousand miles away from here, these two young brothers are bringing people together to support this Boston community the way their community came together to support Michael.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在距离此处千里之外的地方，这两位年轻的兄弟正在号召人们齐心合力支持这个波士顿团体，就像他们当年支持迈克尔一样。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm dead? And so young.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我死了？英年早逝。

yingyinNormal.en: Is that maybe a little young?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这件会不会有点太嫩了。

yingyinNormal.en: She was too young, too gentle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她那么年轻，那么温柔。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey back off. Excuse me, young lady.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嘿，退后，不好意思小姐。

yingyinNormal.en: Young's modulus. Is that right? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杨氏模量对吗？对。

yingyinNormal.en: Either they're too old, or they're too young.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是太老，就是太小。

yingyinNormal.en: Fortunately, our young Mr. Potter discovered it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很幸运的，哈利·波特发现了这件事。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets》

yingyinNormal.en: He's young, Santosh. He's still finding his way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 桑托什，他还小，还在摸索中。

yingyinNormal.en: Come back, so we can be young men together again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 回去吧，重返年轻时。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna keep your young'un out of trouble, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会让您的乖女儿远离麻烦的，老师。

yingyinNormal.en: But now young men like us, aspiring and friendly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然而现在，像我们一样的年轻人，及有上进心，也很友好。

yingyinNormal.en: I have a message for the young people here today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要对今天在座的年轻人说几句。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I think you mean young. He's always been little.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我猜你是说年幼时，他一直很小[个子矮小]。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: We are all becoming increasingly aware of the importance of modeling tolerance and patience for the <highlight>younger</highlight> generation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们都越来越意识到为年轻一代树立宽容和耐心的榜样的重要性。

examination_example.sentence: While their parents were content to work long hours, <highlight>young</highlight> people value flexibility.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然他们的父母满足于长时间工作，但年轻人更看重灵活性。

examination_example.sentence: In Cambodia, the choice of a spouse is a complex one for the <highlight>young</highlight> male.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在柬埔寨，对年轻男性来说，择偶是一件复杂的事情。

sense_info_list.en: recently formed, produced, or come into being

examination_example.sentence: The state's proposed Forest Carbon Plan aims to double efforts to thin out <highlight>young</highlight> trees and clear brush in parts of the forest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该州提出的森林碳计划旨在加倍努力，于部分森林中疏伐幼树和清除灌木。

examination_example.sentence: A Canadian study found that children as <highlight>young</highlight> as 14 months can differentiate between a credible person and a dishonest one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加拿大的一项研究发现，14个月大的幼儿就能区分可信的人和不诚实的人。

examination_example.sentence: Even very <highlight>young</highlight> children tend to look down on the overweight, and teasing about body build has long been a problem in schools.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使是年幼的小孩往往也会看不起超重的人，关于身材的取笑一直是个校园问题。

examination_example.sentence: But while <highlight>young</highlight> and old mostly agree on what constitutes the finish line of a fulfilling life, they offer strikingly different paths for reaching it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是，尽管年轻一辈和老一辈在“什么构成成功人生的终点线”上大体达成共识，他们却提供了截然不同的到达终点线的路径。

examination_example.sentence: Both <highlight>young</highlight> and old agree that getting established is harder for the <highlight>young</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 年轻人和老年人都认为，对年轻人来说，成家立业更难。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Young</highlight> and old converge on one key points.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 年轻人和老年人在一个关键点上达成一致。

word_usage.usage: young可用作表语，也可用作定语。用作定语时后可修饰人或物，如：a young woman一位年轻女子；用作表语时可接介词短语或动词不定式，如：She is young at work. 她没有工作经验。
